     <h1><strong>College Costs </strong></h1> 
     <p>A non-profit corporation, Westmont receives gifts and contributions to help keep costs down. Donations from individuals, churches, and businesses make up the balance and allow the college to offer many types of financial aid.</p> 
     <p>The information below applies to the 2014-2015 academic year. Charges and financial policies are subject to annual change by the board of trustees.</p> 
     <p><strong>2014-2015 costs for a student living on campus</strong> </p> 
     <p>Standard tuition charges cover 1-18 units per semester. Students must petition to take up to 21 units maximum. There will be no extra charge in 2014-2015 for taking more than 18 units.</p> 
